 {"id": "franken_networkx-mgedgeeq", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] MultiGraph.edges(keys=True) == {...} returns False (list-vs-set mismatch)", "description": "nx's MultiEdgeView inherits from Set, so `MG.edges(keys=True) == {(0,1,0),(0,1,1),(1,2,0)}` returns True. fnx returns an `_EdgeListWithSetAlgebra` list subclass; list.__eq__ only supports list-to-list so the same comparison returned False. Added __eq__/__ne__ on _EdgeListWithSetAlgebra that compares as set when RHS is set/frozenset; falls back to list.__eq__ otherwise. Also set __hash__ = None per Python protocol.", "status": "closed", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T08:51:28.310322Z", "close_reason": "Fixed: _EdgeListWithSetAlgebra now compares as set against set/frozenset RHS.", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T08:51:28.310322Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T08:51:28.310322Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-paleydir", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] paley_graph default returns undirected Graph instead of nx's DiGraph", "description": "nx.paley_graph returns a DiGraph by default (edges are symmetric for p \u2261 1 mod 4 and antisymmetric for p \u2261 3 mod 4, but the class is always DiGraph). fnx's Rust fast path returned an undirected Graph, halving the edge count. Fix: always route through the Python fallback with default=DiGraph.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T09:06:52.555584Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T09:06:52.555584Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T09:06:52.555584Z", "close_reason": "Fixed: Python path unconditional so default class + edge set match nx."}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-chordalmg", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] chordal_cycle_graph default returns simple Graph instead of nx's MultiGraph", "description": "nx.chordal_cycle_graph returns a MultiGraph by default \u2014 the (left, right, chord) triple for each node adds self-loops and parallel edges. fnx's Rust fast path returned a simple Graph, dropping parallels. Fix: always route through the Python fallback with default=MultiGraph.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T09:06:52.555584Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T09:06:52.555584Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T09:06:52.555584Z", "close_reason": "Fixed: Python path unconditional so default class + edge set match nx."}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-nvrsub", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] set - G.nodes raises TypeError \u2014 nx.group_betweenness_centrality breaks", "description": "nx.NodeView inherits from collections.abc.Set so `some_set - G.nodes` works via Set.__rsub__. fnx's NodeView raised TypeError: unsupported operand type(s) for -. Broke nx.group_betweenness_centrality (`if set_v - G.nodes:` check). Added __rsub__ / __rand__ / __ror__ / __rxor__ to all NodeView types.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T09:17:03.429962Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T09:17:03.429962Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T09:17:03.429962Z", "close_reason": "Fixed: reflected set-operators now installed on all 4 NodeView types."}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-nbriter", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] G.neighbors returns list instead of iterator \u2014 breaks nx.dfs_labeled_edges", "description": "nx.Graph.neighbors returns a dict_keyiterator; fnx returned a list. The difference broke algorithms that rely on iterator state across for-loop breaks \u2014 notably nx.dfs_labeled_edges (used by chain_decomposition, biconnected_components, etc.). When the algorithm pushed `(start, G.neighbors(start))` onto a stack and later re-entered `for child in children`, the list iteration restarted from the beginning instead of resuming where a `break` left off \u2014 producing spurious nontree edges and wrong chain decompositions. Fix: _neighbors_with_networkx_missing_node_error now wraps list returns in iter() so the result is a proper iterator.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T09:17:03.429962Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T09:17:03.429962Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T09:17:03.429962Z", "close_reason": "Fixed: neighbors wrapper converts list returns to iterators."}
